        "name": "Nimetön",
        "abc": "%%abc-charset utf-8\\n\\nThis file contains 5 frailachs (#1 - #5).\nYou can find more abc tune files at http://www.norbeck.nu/abc/\n\nFrailach (also spelled freilach, freilakh, freylekh, freylech) are klezmer dance tunes.\n\nNote the  key signatures with both sharps and flats. These kinds of scales\ncome from Turkish and Arabic music and are common in klezmer music.\n\nLast updated 23 August 2023.\n\n(c) Copyright 2017-2023 Henrik Norbeck. This file:\n- May be distributed with restrictions below.\n- May not be used for commercial purposes (such as printing a tune book to sell).\n- This file (or parts of it) may not be made available on a web page for\n  download without permission from me.\n- This copyright notice must be kept, except when e-mailing individual tunes.\n- May be printed on paper for personal use.\n- Questions? E-mail: henrik@norbeck.nu\n\nR:frailach\nM:4/4\nL:1/8\nZ:id:hn-%R-%X"
